06:20.680 --> 06:27.460
And here are your hosts. This is

06:27.460 --> 06:36.860
David Crews and Daryl Lane. C. J. Cherryh published her first novel Gate of Ivrel in
1976. It was well received. Cherryh quickly built up a following of readers and was

06:36.860 --> 06:44.420
acknowledged as one of the best new writers around. The popularity of Gate of
Ivrel was one reason Cherryh wrote two others on the same subject to form a

06:44.420 --> 06:53.100
trilogy. The second book was Well of Shiuan and the third Fires of Azeroth. The
trilogy is exciting heroic fantasy that takes place on an alien world. There are

06:53.100 --> 07:01.500
two main characters: Morgaine, a beautiful woman who wields a magic sword, and
Vanye, a man who has vowed to help her in a difficult task. Morgaine's task is to

07:01.500 --> 07:10.880
destroy a space time gate left on Vanye's world. The gate is a still functioning
artifact left by a vanished race, the khal. The gate can be used to travel in time

07:10.880 --> 07:19.960
or space transporting anyone who enters it to other places and times but the
gate and others like it on other planets is a danger to the universe. That sounds

07:19.960 --> 07:27.580
like science fiction but it's not. The story occurs on a primitive planet with no
technology. Vanye and his people regard the gate as an object of magic and

07:27.580 --> 07:36.560
superstitiously avoid it. They also consider Morgaine as an evil sorceress. Her
knowledge of technology to them is simply mysterious magic so the novel is

07:36.560 --> 07:44.020
fantasy. The fighting is done with swords and transportation is by horse. Much of
Cherryh's later writing is straight science fiction with a large amount of hard

07:44.020 --> 07:58.820
science in it we asked her why she started out with fantasy. Well I didn't. Um
they weren't the first books that I had written. There are others which are uh

07:58.820 --> 08:10.680
tentative efforts that uh that didn't pan out in one way or another. Everybody
well I I won't say everybody but a majority of writers tend to have them. My

08:10.680 --> 08:24.900
first love is really technology. The only thing is that I had been out of the
technological mainstream while they had made numerous scientific advances that I

08:24.900 --> 08:37.540
was not current with and it annoys me a great deal to feel that I'm writing
something that is not technically accurate so or that I have glossed over

08:37.540 --> 08:49.900
something it irritates me personally uh to postulate well. For instance we have a
gravity field here which keeps everyone's feet on the deck. I want to know how it

08:49.900 --> 09:04.120
works so uh consequently I I wrote heroic fantasy while I was uh doing a great
deal of reading in Scientific American. Also heroic fantasy is an area where I

09:04.120 --> 09:16.660
have a good deal of expertise since I have a major in classics, history,
archaeology, anthropology, this sort of thing but I'd always been a sort of a

09:16.660 --> 09:25.840
hobbyist in the uh and a little more than a hobbyist since it was one of my
fields. In the history of technology throughout the three books we learned very

09:25.840 --> 09:33.800
little about the background of Morgaine. We asked Cherryh if perhaps Morgaine is a
force or a creature who existed even before the khal, the builders of the gates.

09:33.800 --> 09:43.600
Well actually now there's some of this that I I'm not about to give away uh as
regards to the history of Morgaine because that it gets into the uh the

09:43.600 --> 09:54.640
possibility of a book that I'm working on at the moment. The first set of the
books, the gate books, involve much more the character of Vanye who is a medieval

09:54.640 --> 10:06.220
man. I have to take his viewpoint or they cease to be heroic fantasy and they
begin to be a science fiction novel pure and simple because Morgaine is far more

10:06.220 --> 10:18.020
technologically sophisticated than he is and if it were told from her viewpoint
it would begin to be a thing of numbers and calculus. Um Morgaine is far more

10:18.020 --> 10:28.700
advanced. Exactly where she comes from and what she is I've preferred to leave to
the uh to the reader's estimation, although I will say that your uh your surmises

10:28.700 --> 10:43.600
are fairly well down the center. We'll talk with C. J. Cherryh about some of her
other books next time. This

10:43.600 --> 10:50.940
has been the Science Fiction Radio Show a production of the Permian Basin
Science Fiction Association produced in conjunction with Odessa College in

10:50.940 --> 10:59.700
Odessa, Texas.

